description: Discover world-class design and luxury in this organic contemporary Trousdale masterpiece crafted by award-winning architect Paul McClean and designer Lindsay Chambers and reimagined by Nate Berkus & Jeremiah Brent. Set on a prestigious, quiet cul-de-sac, this 11,000 SF home boasts an architectural exterior with custom Italian stonework. Mid-century-inspired steel grillwork surround the front door that opens to a showstopping glass bridge entrance. The two-story courtyard and walls of glass allow sunlight to fill the home and highlight the beautiful oak ceilings and Travertine walls. Glass walls open to a spectacular outdoor space featuring an expansive infinity pool with city and ocean views and a tranquil Japanese garden. The primary suite sits beside the pool as if it's floating above the water and offers a custom walk-in closet, and spa-like bathroom. Rejuvenate in the marble-clad indoor wellness center with hot and cold plunge, cedar sauna, and gym. Additional amenities include a stunning Nero Marquina-clad bar, home theater, subterranean auto gallery, and fairytale pink playroom. This architecturally significant home is a rare offering, even among the most discerning tastemakers in the city.
